A Family‑Owned Care Coordination Workspace

Families of children with disability are quietly carrying the weight of coordination. Reports scattered across inboxes. Therapists working in silos. Schools missing context. Parents repeating the same story to every new provider. And with NDIS support coordination being reduced, families are expected to manage even more — with fewer resources.

We’re building something different.

A family‑owned care coordination workspace that brings everything together in one safe, simple place. Not a clinical system. Not another app to learn. Not a service that replaces professionals. Just a clear, calm space where the whole team can stay aligned.

At the heart of the workspace are NDIS Goals — because goals drive every plan, every report, every therapy block, and every review. Each goal becomes a living item that links to real‑world evidence: reports, appointments, journal entries, weekly notes, and progress examples. Families finally have a way to show what’s working, what’s changing, and what matters.

The workspace includes:

- A **Care Team Directory** so everyone knows who’s involved
- A **Documents & Reports Library** with plain‑language summaries
- A **Calendar & Appointment Log** that connects sessions to goals
- A **Weekly Notes** page for shared updates
- A **Daily Journal** capturing lived experience
- A **Timeline** showing patterns over time
- And a **Goals & Progress** tracker that ties it all together

It’s simple. It’s secure. It reduces overwhelm. And it gives families something they’ve never had: a single source of truth they control.

This isn’t a tech product pretending to understand disability. It’s a tool built from lived experience — designed to reduce the unpaid labour families are forced to carry, and to make collaboration easier for the people who support them.

We’re starting with a low‑cost Notion‑based pilot so families can use it immediately. As demand grows, we’ll transition to a fully secure Australian‑hosted platform. But the heart of the idea stays the same: **give families clarity, control, and a calmer way to coordinate care.**

If you want to help families feel less alone, less overwhelmed, and more empowered — this is how we start.
